                    <span>  I'm gonna take a stab in the dark and say that Cynthia Kadohata's Newbery winner "Kira-Kira" is a book that you either love or a book that you loathe to the fullest.  Well, I'm a thirteen-year old and I enjoyed it to the fullest.  And what really bugs me is that it is ADULT reviewers who are saying this book is too depressing for children.  ADULT!  Have you people ever heard of Bridge to Terabithia.  It was just as depressing, if not more (though, brilliant I might add).  I'm not even gonna mention last year's Olive's Ocean.
<br />
<br />  I'm a reader and fan of E. Bird's reviews, but she's got this one all wrong (well, except for maybe the bear trap part).  Thank you Amazon, for letting a teen vent!
